metadata.title: OASIS CSDL XML Elements and Attributes Classification
metadata.description: This document lists all EDM elements and categorizes their attribute types. It is based the OASIS OData CSDL XML Representation Version 4.02 specification - Appendix B. and adds the details about values, symbolic references and constraints for attributes.
metadata.source: OASIS OData CSDL XML Representation Version 4.02 specification

basic.name: Basic Attribute
basic.description: Simple value types (strings, booleans, numbers, identifiers)

subcategories.name: simple identifier
subcategories.description: Simple name identifier following XML naming rules

subcategories.name: non-negative integer
subcategories.description: Integer value greater than or equal to zero

subcategories.name: enum
subcategories.description: Value from a predefined set of options

subcategories.name: primitive value
subcategories.description: Basic data type value (string, number, boolean, etc.)

symbolicValues.name: max
symbolicValues.description: shorthand for the maximum length supported by the service

subcategories.name: Scale

symbolicValues.name: floating
symbolicValues.description: decimal floating-point number where precision specifies significant digits (not allowed in OData 4.0 responses)

symbolicValues.name: variable
symbolicValues.description: number of digits to the right of decimal point can vary from zero to the precision value

subcategories.constraints: Scale value MUST be less than or equal to Precision value
subcategories.notes: Services should use lower-case values; clients should accept values case-insensitively

subcategories.name: SRID
subcategories.default: 0 for Geometry types, 4326 for Geography types if not specified

reference.name: Reference Attribute
reference.description: References to other model elements represented in XML/JSON as qualified names, type names, target paths, etc. .

subcategories.name: Absolute Reference
subcategories.description: symbolic references that reference elements anywhere in the model

subcategories.name: Relative Reference
subcategories.description: symbolic references that reference elements relative to a specific ancestor (or related) context element

path.name: Path Attribute
path.description: Path expressions in form of a sequence of model elements represented in XML/JSON as a string or element names with delimiters

subcategories.name: Absolute Path
subcategories.description: Paths that are naming elements by starting from the root of the model

subcategories.name: Relative Path
subcategories.description: Paths that are resolved relative to a specific element context

attributes.name: Namespace
attributes.description: A simple identifier used to uniquely identify the element within its containing scope.

attributes.name: Alias
attributes.description: The alias of a schema MAY be used instead of the namespaceto identify model elements of that schema.

elementGroups.name: Entity Model Elements
elementGroups.description: Core entity and type definition elements

attributes.name: Name
attributes.description: The entity typeâ€™s name that MUST be unique within its schema.

attributes.name: Name
attributes.context: relative to the containing entity/complex type

attributes.name: Type
attributes.description: qualified entity type name or collection thereof

attributes.name: Partner
attributes.context: relative to the target entity type specified in Type attribute

attributes.name: Property
attributes.context: relative to the containing navigation property's source entity type

attributes.name: ReferencedProperty
attributes.context: relative to the containing navigation property's target entity type

attributes.name: Action
attributes.description: action enum: Cascade, None, SetNull, SetDefault

attributes.name: UnderlyingType
attributes.description: qualified name of and integer type
attributes.constraints: restricted to: Edm.Byte, Edm.SByte, Edm.Int16, Edm.Int32, or Edm.Int64

attributes.name: EntitySetPath
attributes.context: relative to the action's parameters when bound

attributes.name: EntitySetPath
attributes.context: relative to the function's parameters when bound

attributes.name: Path
attributes.context: relative to the containing entity set's entity type

attributes.name: Target
attributes.context: relative to the containing entity container

attributes.name: EntitySet
attributes.description: entity set name or target path
attributes.context: relative to the containing entity container

attributes.name: EntitySet
attributes.description: entity set name or target path
attributes.context: relative to the containing entity container

attributes.name: Property
attributes.context: relative path to a property of the type of the enclosing edm:Record expression
